551
00:57:47,308 --> 00:57:49,216
Flynn, go!

552
00:57:53,829 --> 00:57:54,829
Yahhh!

553
00:57:56,445 --> 00:57:59,018
Tron, he fought for me.

554
00:58:00,033 --> 00:58:02,051
I never saw him again.

555
00:58:03,617 --> 00:58:05,205
So why don't you fight?

556
00:58:06,502 --> 00:58:07,502
He did.

557
00:58:07,510 --> 00:58:09,679
It fed from my resistance.

558
00:58:09,680 --> 00:58:12,295
The more I fought, the more powerful
it became.

559
00:58:12,825 --> 00:58:14,751
It was impressive run.

560
00:58:15,810 --> 00:58:20,422
Then my miracle. CLU saw the
ISO's as an imperfection.

561
00:58:21,189 --> 00:58:22,844
So he destroyed them.

562
00:58:26,376 --> 00:58:27,680
The purge.

563
00:58:28,626 --> 00:58:29,958
He killed them all?

564
00:58:30,357 --> 00:58:32,114
It was genocide.

565
00:58:33,836 --> 00:58:36,899
I tried to get back. But I couldn't
get to the portal.

566
00:58:37,473 --> 00:58:40,614
It uses massive power. And it can't
stay open forever.

567
00:58:42,433 --> 00:58:47,257
And like a safe. It can only be opened
from the outside.

568
00:58:49,749 --> 00:58:51,819
It closed on me, Sam.

569
00:58:53,244 --> 00:58:55,009
That's why I never came home.

570
00:59:02,642 --> 00:59:06,075
So the portal. It activated when I came in.

571
00:59:06,541 --> 00:59:07,980
So it's open, now.

572
00:59:07,981 --> 00:59:09,029
Not for long.

573
00:59:09,030 --> 00:59:11,662
Only one millicycle, about eight hours.

574
00:59:11,663 --> 00:59:12,934
So, we go now.

575
00:59:13,482 --> 00:59:15,254
Go home. Make a run for it.

576
00:59:15,255 --> 00:59:16,884
Get you out of here. Don't rush.

577
00:59:16,885 --> 00:59:19,784
What do you mean, don't rush. The
portal's going to close.

578
00:59:21,440 --> 00:59:23,372
What? What is it?

579
00:59:23,374 --> 00:59:27,643
The moment Flynn is on the grid,
CLU will stop at nothing to obtain his disc.

580
00:59:27,644 --> 00:59:31,067
My disc is everything, Sam.
It's the master key.

581
00:59:31,068 --> 00:59:33,077
The golden ticket for the way out.

582
00:59:34,096 --> 00:59:35,670
Not just for me.

583
00:59:35,971 --> 00:59:40,059
You mean all the other... will  make
a landing on those.

584
00:59:40,060 --> 00:59:42,342
CLU figures if I can be in.

585
00:59:42,343 --> 00:59:43,729
Yeah.

586
00:59:43,730 --> 00:59:46,661
With my disc, it's possible.

587
00:59:46,662 --> 00:59:48,024
Then what?

588
00:59:49,007 --> 00:59:50,107
Game over.

589
00:59:51,226 --> 00:59:53,441
The guy doesn't dig imperfection.

590
00:59:55,781 --> 00:59:57,555
What more important is
our world.

591
00:59:59,767 --> 01:00:01,420
I can't let that happen.

592
01:00:01,687 --> 01:00:03,375
I won't.

593
01:00:03,376 --> 01:00:04,631
So what will we do?

594
01:00:05,761 --> 01:00:06,761
Nothing?

595
01:00:06,762 --> 01:00:09,380
It's amazing how productive doing
nothing can be.

596
01:00:09,649 --> 01:00:11,318
CLU's planning something.

597
01:00:11,319 --> 01:00:13,142
We've known that for a while.

598
01:00:13,737 --> 01:00:16,627
Programs have been disappearing,
there's unrest out there.

599
01:00:16,628 --> 01:00:21,700
Even revolution. We sit tight, we might
be brought down from the inside.

600
01:00:22,097 --> 01:00:25,429
The portal's closing. We can't just sit
around. We have to move now.

601
01:00:25,430 --> 01:00:26,465
Tell me.

602
01:00:27,283 --> 01:00:28,527
What brought you here?

603
01:00:28,597 --> 01:00:30,015
Through the grid.

604
01:00:30,803 --> 01:00:32,809
Alan got your page.

605
01:00:32,810 --> 01:00:34,933
I didn't send any page.

606
01:00:34,934 --> 01:00:38,585
It was CLU. CLU sent that page.

607
01:00:38,586 --> 01:00:39,886
That's why you're here.

608
01:00:40,479 --> 01:00:42,485
This is all his design.

609
01:00:42,486 --> 01:00:45,488
He wanted a new piece on the board
to change the game.

610
01:00:46,000 --> 01:00:48,172
With you he got more than he ever dreamed.

611
01:00:48,173 --> 01:00:50,476
This is precisely what he wants.

612
01:00:50,477 --> 01:00:52,695
Us together, heading for the portal.

613
01:00:53,380 --> 01:00:55,018
It's his game now.

614
01:00:55,488 --> 01:00:57,529
The only way to win is not to play.

615
01:00:59,532 --> 01:01:01,670
Now that's a help, great way.

616
01:01:01,675 --> 01:01:03,025
But it is a way.

617
01:01:08,137 --> 01:01:10,507
We need you home.

618
01:01:10,510 --> 01:01:13,105
Don't you want that?

619
01:01:14,255 --> 01:01:17,701
Sometimes life has a way of moving
you past things like wants and hope.

620
01:01:20,208 --> 01:01:21,868
That's right, Dad.

621
01:01:23,052 --> 01:01:24,960
Keep telling yourself that.

622
01:01:31,047 --> 01:01:32,257
Goodnight, Sam.

623
01:01:55,098 --> 01:01:57,855
How can he be so afraid
of his own creation?

624
01:01:57,856 --> 01:02:00,357
I mean, he built CLU.
Why doesn't he just end him.

625
01:02:02,097 --> 01:02:04,355
He could but it would require reintegration.

626
01:02:04,356 --> 01:02:05,384
Yeah, all right.

627
01:02:05,711 --> 01:02:07,889
He would never survive the effect.

628
01:02:07,890 --> 01:02:09,573
It would mean the end of them both.

629
01:02:10,811 --> 01:02:13,163
If he refuses to save himself, then I will.

630
01:02:17,453 --> 01:02:18,453
How?

631
01:02:19,549 --> 01:02:20,949
I'm going to the portal.

632
01:02:21,324 --> 01:02:23,716
CLU wants Dad's death, not mine.

633
01:02:23,717 --> 01:02:27,009
I'm going to fly out I'm going to figure
this thing out from the other side.

634
01:02:27,010 --> 01:02:31,878
If CLU finds a way to my world it will be
gone with one keystroke.

635
01:02:31,880 --> 01:02:34,579
I can't do anything unless I
get to the portal.

636
01:02:36,810 --> 01:02:40,575
He might get stuck, and you don't want to be
stuck in this place for very long.

637
01:02:43,728 --> 01:02:46,615
I really think you should consider
your father's wisdom.

638
01:02:48,518 --> 01:02:49,676
I have.

639
01:03:40,182 --> 01:03:41,391
(Knock on door)

640
01:03:51,708 --> 01:03:53,570
