Wait.

777
01:19:23,751 --> 01:19:25,581
Ever jump a freight train?

778
01:19:27,342 --> 01:19:28,342
Huh?

779
01:19:28,343 --> 01:19:29,728
We do it your way.

780
01:19:29,729 --> 01:19:31,526
It's a long sprint to the portal.

781
01:19:32,054 --> 01:19:34,198
If we beat CLU there we have a chance.

782
01:19:34,199 --> 01:19:35,422
Let's get her out of here.

783
01:19:54,041 --> 01:19:55,996
This will take us there.

784
01:20:22,953 --> 01:20:24,310
Is she going to make it?

785
01:20:24,311 --> 01:20:27,250
I don't know, I gotta identify
the damaged code.

786
01:20:28,288 --> 01:20:31,125
The sequence on it is just
enormously complex.

787
01:20:33,079 --> 01:20:34,209
But didn't you write it?

788
01:20:34,210 --> 01:20:38,358
Some I wrote, the rest of it is just,

789
01:20:40,341 --> 01:20:41,713
beyond me.

790
01:20:44,271 --> 01:20:45,913
She's an Iso.

791
01:20:46,631 --> 01:20:49,240
Yeah, the last Iso.

792
01:20:51,049 --> 01:20:55,286
All this time you were just, protecting her.

793
01:20:55,287 --> 01:20:57,094
She's the miracle, man.

794
01:20:57,409 --> 01:20:59,405
Everything I ever worked for.

795
01:21:00,608 --> 01:21:03,865
A digital frontier to reshape
the human condition.

796
01:21:05,186 --> 01:21:07,751
